The accused are Dean Carl Joseph Haynes, 28, of Sullivan Close, Nottingham; Shaun Tinyick Lau, 28, of Flower and Dean Walk, Tower Hamlets, London; and Christopher Gerald, 21, of Westgate Street, Nottingham, who also faces firearms offences.
Maritia Kirk, of Jedburgh Walk, St Ann's, Nottingham, was charged with firearms offences.
Eight people are currently on bail in connection with the shooting while Nottinghamshire Police carry out further investigations.
The four are due to appear at Nottingham Crown Court on 21 October.
